[4] USA (Oregon)
Date: Sat 14 Jul 2018
Source: KPTV [edited]
http://www.kptv.com/story/38643482/health-officials-confirm-third-case-of-measles-in-portland-metro-area


Multnomah County health officials Fri [13 Jul 2018] confirmed a 3rd case of measles in the Portland metro area. The person was unvaccinated and had been in close contact with a 2nd person diagnosed with measles 6 Jul 2018, according to health officials. Multnomah County Communicable Disease Services has alerted the individual and asked the person to stay home and away from other people.

The 3 cases in Multnomah County are in addition to a related but unconfirmed case in a young child that is under investigation in Clark County, Washington. Clark County health officials identified 3 locations where people may have been exposed and, on Fri [13 Jul], identified a 4th. [See URL above for locations where individuals may have been exposed to measles virus.]

Health officials note that the risk of exposure is incredibly low. The 1st case in Multnomah County was confirmed 27 Jun 2018. It was the 1st confirmed case in the Portland metro area since 2014. Despite the case confirmed, health officials don't believe anyone else has been exposed to measles in Multnomah County.

