[6] Pakistan
Date: Mon 16 Jul 2018
Source: The Express Tribune [edited]
https://tribune.com.pk/story/1759059/1-three-children-infected-measles/


At least 3 children have been infected with measles in Multan on Sun [15 Jul 2018], Express News reported. Doctors at Children's Complex said that [children aged] 2 years, 3 years, and 9 months were admitted to the health facility after catching the virus. They said all the patients were being provided treatment and were being kept in the isolation ward at the hospital.

Earlier, a report released by WHO revealed that 5871 cases of measles were reported in Pakistan in 2016. The figure almost doubled in 2017 to 10 540 cases, while laboratory tests confirmed 2806 and 6437 reported cases in 2016 and 2017, respectively.

According to WHO standards, 95 per cent vaccine coverage is the rate necessary to avert an outbreak, as the disease is highly infectious. Even reaching an 80 per cent coverage threshold will avert large-scale outbreaks.

Last year [2017], a meeting conducted by the Pakistan Health and Population Strategic Forum, chaired by federal minister for national health services Saira Afzal Tarar, took notice of the measles situation. She agreed to launch a nationwide anti-measles drive in October 2018. They also decided to release a plan of action with mutual consultation among all provinces.

